Penn West Petroleum Ltd. Case Solution & Answer
Case Study Analysis Solutions
 

This Case is about  FINANCIAL MARKETS
PUBLICATION DATE: July 31, 2015 PRODUCT #: W15336-PDF-ENG
Penn West, a Canadian oil company, made numerous acquisitions that led to a buildup of goodwill. There was worry this goodwill had been impaired when the economic environment deteriorated.
The concern deepened as economic variables improved but the stock operation of Penn West continued to be inferior, suggesting the market considered the business was possibly overvalued. It was becoming clear that Penn West had been too confident in its predictions affecting revenue flows from its properties. Would the business be able to move forward? How?

